                "display_name": "Ian Webster",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "ian@promptfoo.dev"
            },
            "text": "I did have one other question.",
            "timestamp": "00:06:31"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Ian Webster",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "ian@promptfoo.dev"
            },
            "text": "So usually when we are going to productionize an article, like now these are just big blocks of text.",
            "timestamp": "00:06:34"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Ian Webster",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "ian@promptfoo.dev"
            },
            "text": "Usually we break it out with diagrams or images or that kind of thing.",
            "timestamp": "00:06:45"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Ian Webster",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "ian@promptfoo.dev"
            },
            "text": "I'm wondering if that's something that you guys can do, otherwise it's something that we would probably be doing manually on our side.",
            "timestamp": "00:06:50"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Ian Webster",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "ian@promptfoo.dev"
            },
            "text": "I'm not saying like I don't want like an AI-generated image for each section or just like sometimes there are visual aids or images from like the internet that are applicable, that kind of thing.",
            "timestamp": "00:07:00"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Vivek Shankar",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "vivek@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "One thing that you guys could do if it's in two parts here, if it's something that refers to the existing resource of the internet, we can definitely do it within the text.",
            "timestamp": "00:07:11"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Vivek Shankar",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "vivek@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "We can review all the articles just to make sure you know where they go and make sense.",
            "timestamp": "00:07:30"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Vivek Shankar",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "vivek@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "In terms of actually creating images correctly, I think that would be a heavier look for us.",
            "timestamp": "00:07:34"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Vivek Shankar",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "vivek@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "We don't have the graphic design side of things over here.",
            "timestamp": "00:07:44"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "Yeah, it's growing to be more and more of a common trend we're looking to address across accounts, especially those that skew more on the technical side and want to give more specificity.",
            "timestamp": "00:07:48"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "examples, it presents an interesting challenge.",
            "timestamp": "00:08:00"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "We've done this in a few different ways.",
            "timestamp": "00:08:05"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "At times, what we've done with those accounts is that they lean on doing some sort of like pillar piece that's a bit more in depth that they're owning more from like a like you have that deep product, knowledge, part of marketing lens and then we're building clusters around it and those clusters tend to need less of that.",
            "timestamp": "00:08:07"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "It's an opportunity for us to like still provide value and solve for some of those, particularly in this case, I'm not sure that really works or not, but just sharing it like there's a lot of different options pointing.",
            "timestamp": "00:08:24"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "But yeah, when it comes to creative resources, it is a bit of a challenge for us for sure, just in the way we structure, we're likely going to start, you know, bringing on a lead for as a creative director and help us build that out over time.",
            "timestamp": "00:08:36"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "But what we've done in the interim is essentially would probably doesn't fulfill what you're after is, you know, outside of images we can find across the internet, you know,",
            "timestamp": "00:08:50"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "either stock, AI-generated, or a bit of a combination of elements from the brand, from our clients, from things like their stigma, using iconography, things of that nature, and then kind of treating those as wrapping elements around AI-generated.",
            "timestamp": "00:09:00"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "And there's different things we can do around AI-generated to make it look brand, feel-wise acceptable for some of our accounts, but every account's different.",
            "timestamp": "00:09:16"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "Some are like, I absolutely want no images that are AI-generated.",
            "timestamp": "00:09:26"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "It's completely, it doesn't work with our brand.",
            "timestamp": "00:09:28"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "But when it comes to diagrams, doesn't necessarily interesting challenge, because, yeah, they don't tend to do super well with direction when it comes to, it's getting better from what I'm understanding, and I'm seeing some here and there, but, you know, some of the classic challenges in the early days of AI-generated images seem to continue to hold.",
            "timestamp": "00:09:31"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "But we can take it back and explore solutions, but I think, yeah, my assumption here is, we don't",
            "timestamp": "00:09:55"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "that lean on either things you have in the library standpoint or on other pieces of content that we can repurpose and then similarly can we fill in the gaps looking for internet sources.",
            "timestamp": "00:10:00"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "We are also looking to build use cases with another one of our clients, DataGrid, who's doing a lot of agentic AI based things and develop different use cases of workflows with them.",
            "timestamp": "00:10:13"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "One of those use cases we're exploring is helping us identify images at scale in a variety of ways in relation to the articles but that's probably a future forward thing but just more over sharing that.",
            "timestamp": "00:10:26"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "We're trying to attack this from multiple angles.",
            "timestamp": "00:10:39"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "This specific example you're talking about, we don't have the the most ideal answer for today.",
            "timestamp": "00:10:42"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Kyle Gaudreau",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "kyle@growthxlabs.com"
            },
            "text": "Okay, well thank you.",
            "timestamp": "00:10:48"
        },
        {
            "speaker": {
                "display_name": "Ian Webster",
                "matched_calendar_invitee_email": "ian@promptfoo.dev"
            },
            "text": "We'll look at these articles.",
